column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

Tamworth penned 1475  good quality cattle which included a very good penning of feeder steers and processor cows. The regular buyers attended and operated to a generally dearer market.

Weaner cattle sold to a dearer result steers 322c to 402c/kg and heifers to 326c/kg all to restockers. Light steers to feed on 284c to 372c/kg backgrounders 260c to 358c/kg. Medium feeders were significantly dearer as well as heavy steers. Heifers sold to similar trends the light drafts to feed 296c to 342c/kg the background heifers following suit. Medium weight feeder heifers were dearer selling up to 20c/kg better. Heavy heifers sold to 270c/kg.

Not many heavy grown steers to quote the heifer portion selling 230c to 290c/kg. All cow categories sold strongly with the heavy drafts 15c to 20c/kg better the heavy cows making to 249c/kg.

Stephen  Adams   MLA
